ow ground. It can be easily noticed in moist habitat in and around forest, grassland, on tree trunks due to their peculiar appearance. Present communication discusses important habit and habitats, medicinal and culinary uses, status of mushrooms in Ethiopia, and sustainable use for sustenance and food security. Keywords : Mushroom, Fungus, Status, Tigray, Ethiopia.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Semwal","given":"K. C.","literal":""},{"family":"Semwal","given":"K. C.","literal":""},{"family":"Lemma","given":"H.","literal":""},{"family":"Lemma","given":"H.","literal":""},{"family":"Dhyani","given":"Anurag","literal":""},{"family":"Dhyani","given":"Anurag","literal":""},{"family":"Equar","given":"G.","literal":""},{"family":"Equar","given":"G.","literal":""},{"family":"Amhare","given":"S.","literal":""},{"family":"Amhare","given":"S.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"semwal_mushroom_2014","year":"2014","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Mushroom: Nature’s Treasure in Ethiopia"],"author-links":["[[Author/K. C. Semwal]]","[[Author/K. C. Semwal]]","[[Author/H. Lemma]]","[[Author/H. Lemma]]","[[Author/Anurag Dhyani]]","[[Author/Anurag Dhyani]]","[[Author/G. Equar]]","[[Author/G. Equar]]","[[Author/S. Amhare]]","[[Author/S. Amhare]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/semwal_mushroom_2014/semwal_mushroom_2014.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1y36p4o","at":1774951886691}},"smart_blocks:Research/@semwal_mushroom_2014.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.05588431,-0.01083184,0.04863172,-0.03115323,0.03667587,-0.0390679,0.02821371,0.0248141,-0.02656366,0.10219606,0.02599344,-0.09624872,0.03323075,0.02675391,0.03800988,0.0477174,0.01368735,-0.00258625,-0.04551507,0.0371867,0.11552329,-0.02116326,0.03543178,-0.03090054,0.06741435,0.02587641,-0.06170191,-0.0472827,-0.01994644,-0.21410137,0.00796767,0.0539216,0.04078748,-0.02424519,